        "text": "## Fe³⁺ Complex Stability: EDTA vs NTA\n\n### log K₁ Side-by-Side (β_def_812: Fe³⁺ + L⁴⁻/L³⁻ ⇌ [FeL])\n\n| Ligand | Full Name | log K₁ | T (°C) | I (M) | Equation |\n|--------|-----------|--------|--------|-------|----------|\n| **EDTA** | Ethylenedinitrilotetraacetic acid | **25.1** | 25 | 0.1 | Fe³⁺ + L ⇌ [FeL] |\n| **NTA** | Nitrilotriacetic acid | **15.9** | 25 | 0.1 | Fe³⁺ + L ⇌ [FeL] |\n\n> Both values are from SRD-46 (beta_def_812, aqueous, 25 °C, I = 0.1 M), making them directly comparable.\n\nAt higher ionic strength (I = 1.0 M), the values shift to **23.8** (EDTA) and **14.78** (NTA) — the ~9 log-unit gap is remarkably consistent across conditions.",
